*sass-3.1.19 (25 Jun 2012)

  25 Jun 2012; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org> +sass-3.1.19.ebuild:
  Version bump. Avoid known-to-be-broken tests on jruby. Fixes bug 422937.

  02 Jun 2012; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org> -sass-3.1.4.ebuild,
  -sass-3.1.5.ebuild, -sass-3.1.10.ebuild, -sass-3.1.10-r1.ebuild,
  -sass-3.1.12.ebuild:
  Remove old versions.

*sass-3.1.17 (11 May 2012)

  11 May 2012; Diego E. Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org> +sass-3.1.17.ebuild:
  Version bump; forgo tests when using JRuby for now.

  01 Mar 2012; Fabian Groffen <grobian@gentoo.org> sass-3.1.12.ebuild,
  sass-3.1.15.ebuild:
  Marked ~x64-macos

*sass-3.1.15 (28 Feb 2012)

  28 Feb 2012; Diego E. Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org> +sass-3.1.15.ebuild:
  Version bump; tests are known not to work on JRuby for now, working on it.

*sass-3.1.12 (22 Jan 2012)

  22 Jan 2012; Diego E. Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org> +sass-3.1.12.ebuild:
  Version bump.

*sass-3.1.10-r1 (30 Dec 2011)

  30 Dec 2011; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org> +sass-3.1.10-r1.ebuild:
  Avoid yard documentation task which causes segmentation fault. Add ruby19.
  Avoid tests depending on fixed hash ordering.

